hence it was reintroduced to England from the early 20th century. It is now very widely used in England, Wales, and elsewhere in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Gawain","meanings":["Of Celtic origin, but uncertain ultimate derivation; it first appears in French sources as <i>Gauvain</i>. The name is borne in the Arthurian romances by one of the knights of the Round Table (more familiar in English versions as Sir  <b>Gawain</b> ). It was still in use in the north of England as late as the early 18th century and never died out in Scotland, whence it was reintroduced to England from the early 20th century. It is now very widely used in England, Wales, and elsewhere in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Gavin Baird of Posso was born in 1400, in Peeblesshire, Scotland, his father, Gavin William de Baird, was 45 and his mother, Janet Cochran, was 46. He married Elizabeth Gordon in 1434, in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1478, in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland, at the age of 78, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1400–1478":"1400–1478","1370–1397":"1370–1397","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1434–1503":"1434–1503","1355–1458":"1355–1458","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1503":"1503","1458":"1458","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","before 1370":"enne 1370","1370":"1370","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","England":"England","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1400–1478":"1400–1478","1370–1397":"1370–1397","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1434–1503":"1434–1503","1355–1458":"1355–1458","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1503":"1503","1458":"1458","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","before 1370":"ennen vuotta 1370","1370":"1370","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","England":"England","Sc